00:01:14.109 --> 00:01:15.400 align:middle line:90%
>>It's all right if I stand up?

00:01:15.400 --> 00:01:16.200 align:middle line:90%
>>Absolutely.

00:01:16.200 --> 00:01:17.350 align:middle line:90%
>>I'll be more comfortable.

00:01:17.350 --> 00:01:21.550 align:middle line:84%
Well, I was thinking
as I was traveling

00:01:21.550 --> 00:01:25.470 align:middle line:84%
to New York-- because we hadn't
actually announced the topic--

00:01:25.470 --> 00:01:30.000 align:middle line:84%
or I wasn't aware of what
the topic was going to be--

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:40.810 align:middle line:84%
but what I was struggling with
was the idea that-- looking

00:01:40.810 --> 00:01:46.420 align:middle line:84%
back at my own life,
personally, I've been always

00:01:46.420 --> 00:01:49.720 align:middle line:84%
interested in the abstract,
in the metaphysical,

00:01:49.720 --> 00:01:56.420 align:middle line:84%
in these great journeys into
the infinite and the unbounded

00:01:56.420 --> 00:02:01.280 align:middle line:84%
and the eternal, and trying to
figure it out intellectually.

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:05.390 align:middle line:84%
And about less
than a year ago-- I

00:02:05.390 --> 00:02:07.700 align:middle line:84%
don't know the exact date--
I was at the Royal Albert

00:02:07.700 --> 00:02:10.419 align:middle line:84%
Hall in England and
happened to have

00:02:10.419 --> 00:02:16.050 align:middle line:84%
a very wonderful private
meeting with His Holiness

00:02:16.050 --> 00:02:17.580 align:middle line:90%
the Dalai Lama.

00:02:17.580 --> 00:02:20.920 align:middle line:84%
And we got into some
abstract discussions--

00:02:20.920 --> 00:02:25.430 align:middle line:84%
because that's where I always
direct people, even the Dalai

00:02:25.430 --> 00:02:27.540 align:middle line:90%
Lama.

00:02:27.540 --> 00:02:29.390 align:middle line:84%
And he stopped me
in the middle of it

00:02:29.390 --> 00:02:32.540 align:middle line:84%
and he said, it's
interesting, and one

00:02:32.540 --> 00:02:36.870 align:middle line:84%
can go on into
abstractions forever,

00:02:36.870 --> 00:02:39.360 align:middle line:90%
but how does it change our life?

00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:45.680 align:middle line:84%
And how does
knowing what you are

00:02:45.680 --> 00:02:49.100 align:middle line:84%
trying to express
right now-- how does it

00:02:49.100 --> 00:02:51.420 align:middle line:90%
change people's lives?

00:02:51.420 --> 00:02:55.110 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that His
Holiness-- even though he

00:02:55.110 --> 00:03:03.130 align:middle line:84%
can if he wants to take the
same journeys even into a more

00:03:03.130 --> 00:03:07.920 align:middle line:84%
extended domain of awareness--
that he's a very practical man.

00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:10.670 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately
what really matters

00:03:10.670 --> 00:03:15.800 align:middle line:84%
is the essence of Buddhism is
the alleviation of suffering.

00:03:15.800 --> 00:03:20.620 align:middle line:84%
Even the Buddha
himself was not really

00:03:20.620 --> 00:03:27.442 align:middle line:84%
interested in the abstractions
of reincarnation theories

00:03:27.442 --> 00:03:30.630 align:middle line:84%
or the different
realms of being--

00:03:30.630 --> 00:03:33.840 align:middle line:84%
even though Tibetan Buddhism
is the authority in all

00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:35.970 align:middle line:90%
of those areas.

00:03:35.970 --> 00:03:41.930 align:middle line:84%
The Buddha himself was only
interested in one question--

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:44.950 align:middle line:84%
what is the cause
of human suffering,

00:03:44.950 --> 00:03:48.080 align:middle line:90%
and what is the way out of it?

00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:51.670 align:middle line:84%
That's the essence of
Buddhism basically.

00:03:51.670 --> 00:03:55.710 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm not going to
steal the thunder from Bob--

00:03:55.710 --> 00:03:56.510 align:middle line:90%
>>Steal away.

00:03:56.510 --> 00:03:59.090 align:middle line:84%
>>--who's the
expert in this area,

00:03:59.090 --> 00:04:02.950 align:middle line:84%
but I'd like to start off with
just that one question from

00:04:02.950 --> 00:04:04.530 align:middle line:90%
a Vedantic perspective.

00:04:04.530 --> 00:04:05.330 align:middle line:90%
>>Please.

00:04:05.330 --> 00:04:07.790 align:middle line:84%
>>Then perhaps what
we can do is draw

00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:10.520 align:middle line:84%
the parallels between
Vedanta and Buddhism

00:04:10.520 --> 00:04:11.490 align:middle line:90%
if that's all right.

00:04:11.490 --> 00:04:12.290 align:middle line:90%
>>Absolutely.

00:04:12.290 --> 00:04:16.930 align:middle line:84%
>>Because essentially it's a
question of semantics, I think.

00:04:16.930 --> 00:04:21.720 align:middle line:84%
So Vedanta, which is the great
wisdom tradition of India that

00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:30.800 align:middle line:84%
goes back at least 1500 BC--
and the authors of the Vedanta

00:04:30.800 --> 00:04:38.050 align:middle line:84%
are the great Rishis who
span several eras of time,

00:04:38.050 --> 00:04:41.110 align:middle line:84%
especially the ones who
wrote the Upanishads.

00:04:41.110 --> 00:04:44.850 align:middle line:84%
If I could summarize
what Vedanta says about

00:04:44.850 --> 00:04:47.940 align:middle line:84%
the subject-- and, in fact,
if I could summarize the whole

00:04:47.940 --> 00:04:51.900 align:middle line:84%
of Vedanta in the
next 10 minutes--

00:04:51.900 --> 00:04:53.110 align:middle line:90%
it would be as follows--

00:04:53.110 --> 00:04:56.170 align:middle line:90%


00:04:56.170 --> 00:05:00.630 align:middle line:84%
Vedanta says that there
are five reasons why

00:05:00.630 --> 00:05:04.330 align:middle line:84%
human beings suffer,
and these five

00:05:04.330 --> 00:05:06.660 align:middle line:90%
are called kleshas in Sanskrit.

00:05:06.660 --> 00:05:13.780 align:middle line:84%
K-L-E-S-H-A-S. The first klesha,
or the first cause of human

00:05:13.780 --> 00:05:20.460 align:middle line:84%
suffering, is not knowing
the true nature of reality.

00:05:20.460 --> 00:05:25.350 align:middle line:84%
Number one-- not knowing
the true nature of reality.

00:05:25.350 --> 00:05:31.710 align:middle line:84%
The second klesha-- number
two-- is clinging to or grasping

00:05:31.710 --> 00:05:37.820 align:middle line:84%
or holding on to that which
is ephemeral, transitory,

00:05:37.820 --> 00:05:44.378 align:middle line:84%
illusionary, insubstantial,
and therefore not real.

00:05:44.378 --> 00:05:47.160 align:middle line:90%
The second cause of suffering.

00:05:47.160 --> 00:05:51.360 align:middle line:84%
The third cause of suffering--
the third klesha-- is aversion

00:05:51.360 --> 00:05:57.840 align:middle line:84%
to, revulsion to,
fear from, or fear

00:05:57.840 --> 00:06:07.330 align:middle line:84%
of that which is insubstantial,
transitory ephemeral, not real,

00:06:07.330 --> 00:06:09.680 align:middle line:90%
illusionary.

00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:13.960 align:middle line:84%
The fourth cause of
suffering is identification

00:06:13.960 --> 00:06:18.210 align:middle line:84%
with the false and
constricted and habitual self,

00:06:18.210 --> 00:06:21.470 align:middle line:90%
which we call the ego.

00:06:21.470 --> 00:06:25.310 align:middle line:84%
And the fifth cause of
suffering-- the fifth klesha--

00:06:25.310 --> 00:06:28.410 align:middle line:90%
is the fear of death.

00:06:28.410 --> 00:06:31.270 align:middle line:90%
And Vedanta says, that's it.

00:06:31.270 --> 00:06:35.120 align:middle line:84%
These are the five reasons
why humans suffer--

00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:37.800 align:middle line:84%
not knowing the true
nature of reality,

00:06:37.800 --> 00:06:40.200 align:middle line:84%
grasping to things
that aren't real,

00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:44.220 align:middle line:84%
running away from and fearing
things that are not real,

00:06:44.220 --> 00:06:48.910 align:middle line:84%
identification
with a false self--

00:06:48.910 --> 00:06:53.160 align:middle line:84%
a constricted self--
and the fear of death.

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:54.380 align:middle line:90%
Period.

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:59.010 align:middle line:84%
All other causes of suffering
can be somehow connected

00:06:59.010 --> 00:07:00.360 align:middle line:90%
to these five.

00:07:00.360 --> 00:07:04.010 align:middle line:84%
And then Vedanta goes on
to say that these five are

00:07:04.010 --> 00:07:07.040 align:middle line:90%
contained in the first one.

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:09.890 align:middle line:84%
The five kleshas are
contained in the first one.

00:07:09.890 --> 00:07:12.800 align:middle line:84%
So the only cause
of suffering is not

00:07:12.800 --> 00:07:16.720 align:middle line:84%
knowing the true
nature of reality.

00:07:16.720 --> 00:07:18.790 align:middle line:84%
The only cause of
suffering is not

00:07:18.790 --> 00:07:21.140 align:middle line:84%
knowing the true
nature of reality.

00:07:21.140 --> 00:07:25.390 align:middle line:84%
Vedanta says the true nature
of reality is Brahman.

00:07:25.390 --> 00:07:29.160 align:middle line:84%
Brahman is a word,
like any other.

00:07:29.160 --> 00:07:32.805 align:middle line:84%
And if you ask a Vedantist
to describe it, he can't.

00:07:32.805 --> 00:07:37.560 align:middle line:84%
He says he/she cannot
describe what Brahman is,

00:07:37.560 --> 00:07:40.160 align:middle line:90%
except to call it that.

00:07:40.160 --> 00:07:42.790 align:middle line:90%
T-H-A-T. The English word that.

00:07:42.790 --> 00:07:44.100 align:middle line:90%
In Sanskrit, tat.

00:07:44.100 --> 00:07:44.900 align:middle line:90%
>>Tat.

00:07:44.900 --> 00:07:46.070 align:middle line:90%
>>Tat.

00:07:46.070 --> 00:07:49.020 align:middle line:84%
And Vedanta says, I am that,
you are that, all this is

00:07:49.020 --> 00:07:51.300 align:middle line:90%
that, that's all there is.

00:07:51.300 --> 00:07:53.469 align:middle line:84%
And if you really,
really get that, then I

00:07:53.469 --> 00:07:54.510 align:middle line:90%
have nothing more to say.

00:07:54.510 --> 00:07:55.010 align:middle line:90%
Good night.

00:07:55.010 --> 00:07:55.810 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for coming.

00:07:55.810 --> 00:07:57.330 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:07:57.330 --> 00:07:58.800 align:middle line:90%


00:07:58.800 --> 00:08:01.410 align:middle line:84%
Vedantists refer
to Brahman as that.

00:08:01.410 --> 00:08:02.480 align:middle line:90%
It's infinite.

00:08:02.480 --> 00:08:03.920 align:middle line:90%
It's immortal.

00:08:03.920 --> 00:08:04.960 align:middle line:90%
It's eternal.

00:08:04.960 --> 00:08:06.510 align:middle line:90%
It's ineffable.

00:08:06.510 --> 00:08:08.060 align:middle line:90%
It's unbounded.

00:08:08.060 --> 00:08:09.340 align:middle line:90%
It is silent.

00:08:09.340 --> 00:08:12.410 align:middle line:90%
It has infinite dynamism.

00:08:12.410 --> 00:08:15.050 align:middle line:90%
It has infinite intelligence.

00:08:15.050 --> 00:08:19.860 align:middle line:90%
And it is it, whatever it is.

00:08:19.860 --> 00:08:24.580 align:middle line:84%
And this Brahman projects
itself as the universe

00:08:24.580 --> 00:08:27.330 align:middle line:84%
through what is called
the power of Maya.

00:08:27.330 --> 00:08:31.320 align:middle line:84%
Brahman projects itself
as the physical universe,

00:08:31.320 --> 00:08:36.419 align:middle line:84%
including you and me,
through the power of Maya.

00:08:36.419 --> 00:08:39.549 align:middle line:84%
The word Maya means--
technically, etymologically--

00:08:39.549 --> 00:08:43.880 align:middle line:84%
it means measurement, although
it's translated frequently

00:08:43.880 --> 00:08:49.260 align:middle line:84%
as illusion, because what you're
trying to measure is eternity,

00:08:49.260 --> 00:08:50.420 align:middle line:90%
or the infinite.

00:08:50.420 --> 00:08:52.400 align:middle line:84%
And in the measurement
of the infinite,

00:08:52.400 --> 00:08:55.690 align:middle line:84%
you create the concept of
time and you give birth

00:08:55.690 --> 00:08:57.860 align:middle line:90%
to the relative universe.

00:08:57.860 --> 00:09:02.540 align:middle line:84%
So Maya, measurement, meter--
the English word meter,

00:09:02.540 --> 00:09:06.750 align:middle line:84%
which also is something you
use to measure-- Maya, meter,

00:09:06.750 --> 00:09:11.780 align:middle line:84%
measurement, time,
music, matter, all refer

00:09:11.780 --> 00:09:14.820 align:middle line:84%
to the womb of creation, which
is the infinite, unbounded womb

00:09:14.820 --> 00:09:17.030 align:middle line:84%
of creation which
projects itself

00:09:17.030 --> 00:09:21.270 align:middle line:84%
through the power of Maya
into the realm of space-time

00:09:21.270 --> 00:09:23.660 align:middle line:90%
and causation.

00:09:23.660 --> 00:09:29.580 align:middle line:84%
And it does so through
the web of karma.

00:09:29.580 --> 00:09:34.720 align:middle line:84%
Karma is our own past actions
on an individual level,

00:09:34.720 --> 00:09:37.500 align:middle line:84%
but also on a collective
level, and ultimately

00:09:37.500 --> 00:09:40.940 align:middle line:84%
from a deeper, more
mythical level.

00:09:40.940 --> 00:09:44.820 align:middle line:84%
The remnants of karma--
our past actions-- they

00:09:44.820 --> 00:09:47.920 align:middle line:84%
are like seeds in
our consciousness.

00:09:47.920 --> 00:09:50.310 align:middle line:84%
And these remnants
of karma constantly

00:09:50.310 --> 00:09:55.940 align:middle line:84%
actualize into our consciousness
as our subjective experience.

00:09:55.940 --> 00:10:01.460 align:middle line:84%
They're just the seeds of past
memories, past experiences.

00:10:01.460 --> 00:10:03.330 align:middle line:84%
They're not the
memories themselves.

00:10:03.330 --> 00:10:07.090 align:middle line:90%
They are virtual memories.

00:10:07.090 --> 00:10:10.370 align:middle line:84%
Just like you have virtual
photons and virtual particles,

00:10:10.370 --> 00:10:13.210 align:middle line:84%
they're virtual memories
that don't actually

00:10:13.210 --> 00:10:14.920 align:middle line:84%
exist in the brain,
because they are part

00:10:14.920 --> 00:10:18.440 align:middle line:90%
of the software of our souls.

00:10:18.440 --> 00:10:21.900 align:middle line:84%
I was watching the other
day on "60 minutes"

00:10:21.900 --> 00:10:26.510 align:middle line:84%
the person who just wrote
Mr. Reagan's biography.

00:10:26.510 --> 00:10:28.065 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you
saw that program,

00:10:28.065 --> 00:10:30.360 align:middle line:84%
but there's a very
poignant moment

00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:34.350 align:middle line:84%
in the program where
he says that he's

00:10:34.350 --> 00:10:36.490 align:middle line:90%
a family friend of Mr. Reagan.

00:10:36.490 --> 00:10:38.690 align:middle line:84%
And apparently Mr.
Reagan recently

00:10:38.690 --> 00:10:40.930 align:middle line:90%
came from a therapy session.

00:10:40.930 --> 00:10:44.720 align:middle line:84%
And somebody had left
a toy White House

00:10:44.720 --> 00:10:47.510 align:middle line:90%
next to the fish tank.

00:10:47.510 --> 00:10:51.980 align:middle line:84%
And Mr. Reagan was
clutching onto it--

00:10:51.980 --> 00:10:53.850 align:middle line:90%
holding onto it when he came.

00:10:53.850 --> 00:10:57.260 align:middle line:84%
And Nancy Reagan tried
to pry his fingers open,

00:10:57.260 --> 00:10:58.690 align:middle line:90%
and he wouldn't let go of it.

00:10:58.690 --> 00:11:00.340 align:middle line:84%
And finally she
said to him, Ronnie,

00:11:00.340 --> 00:11:02.180 align:middle line:90%
what's that in your hand?

00:11:02.180 --> 00:11:06.180 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at it for a
minute or so, and he said,

00:11:06.180 --> 00:11:07.700 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
it is, but I think

00:11:07.700 --> 00:11:10.880 align:middle line:90%
it has something to do with me.

00:11:10.880 --> 00:11:14.350 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
it is, but I think

00:11:14.350 --> 00:11:15.790 align:middle line:90%
it has something to do with me.

00:11:15.790 --> 00:11:17.640 align:middle line:90%
That's what a sanskara is.

00:11:17.640 --> 00:11:20.250 align:middle line:84%
That's what a
potential memory is.

00:11:20.250 --> 00:11:22.870 align:middle line:90%
That's the remnant of karma.

00:11:22.870 --> 00:11:27.320 align:middle line:84%
And I looked at that program
and realized we all have

00:11:27.320 --> 00:11:28.340 align:middle line:90%
Alzheimer's.

00:11:28.340 --> 00:11:29.890 align:middle line:90%
All of us.

00:11:29.890 --> 00:11:31.516 align:middle line:84%
We all have spiritual
Alzheimer's.

00:11:31.516 --> 00:11:32.890 align:middle line:84%
>>I'm very relieved
to hear that.

00:11:32.890 --> 00:11:33.690 align:middle line:90%
>>OK.

00:11:33.690 --> 00:11:35.070 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:35.070 --> 00:11:36.030 align:middle line:90%


00:11:36.030 --> 00:11:37.220 align:middle line:90%
>>I thought it was only me.

00:11:37.220 --> 00:11:38.180 align:middle line:90%
>>Yeah.

00:11:38.180 --> 00:11:40.120 align:middle line:90%
We have this memory.

00:11:40.120 --> 00:11:43.430 align:middle line:84%
We have this faint memory
that somewhere there

00:11:43.430 --> 00:11:46.690 align:middle line:84%
is a soul over here--
a faint memory that

00:11:46.690 --> 00:11:49.230 align:middle line:90%
somewhere there's a soul here.

00:11:49.230 --> 00:11:52.960 align:middle line:84%
We know it has
something to do with me,

00:11:52.960 --> 00:11:56.000 align:middle line:90%
and we have no idea what it is.

00:11:56.000 --> 00:12:01.500 align:middle line:84%
And that's what Vedanta says is
the cause of all our suffering.

00:12:01.500 --> 00:12:03.870 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the Bible
says that, too.

00:12:03.870 --> 00:12:08.890 align:middle line:84%
What good does it do a man
to find the whole world

00:12:08.890 --> 00:12:11.160 align:middle line:90%
but lose his own soul?

00:12:11.160 --> 00:12:16.460 align:middle line:84%
And losing the soul,
we begin to have

00:12:16.460 --> 00:12:18.630 align:middle line:90%
the experience of suffering.

00:12:18.630 --> 00:12:22.060 align:middle line:84%
So this karmic software,
which is constantly

00:12:22.060 --> 00:12:24.680 align:middle line:84%
actualizing into
our consciousness,

00:12:24.680 --> 00:12:28.950 align:middle line:84%
it appears as our own thoughts,
our own memories, our desires,

00:12:28.950 --> 00:12:31.360 align:middle line:90%
our feelings, our emotions.

00:12:31.360 --> 00:12:34.860 align:middle line:84%
And during the daytime what
we do is-- our rational mind,

00:12:34.860 --> 00:12:38.800 align:middle line:84%
it weaves stories around
this karmic software.

00:12:38.800 --> 00:12:43.170 align:middle line:84%
It does so quite logically,
at least to the rational mind.

00:12:43.170 --> 00:12:45.000 align:middle line:90%
And we live out these stories.

00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:48.450 align:middle line:90%
We call them everyday reality.

00:12:48.450 --> 00:12:50.860 align:middle line:84%
And the same thing
happens at night,

00:12:50.860 --> 00:12:53.500 align:middle line:90%
but the rational mind is asleep.

00:12:53.500 --> 00:12:58.580 align:middle line:84%
And so there is not a consistent
logic to the stories at night,

00:12:58.580 --> 00:13:01.030 align:middle line:90%
and we call them dreams.

00:13:01.030 --> 00:13:05.850 align:middle line:84%
But Vedanta says the mechanics
of the dream and the mechanics

00:13:05.850 --> 00:13:12.230 align:middle line:84%
of waking state of
consciousness, it's the same.

00:13:12.230 --> 00:13:14.890 align:middle line:84%
One is being given a
rationalization and the other

00:13:14.890 --> 00:13:19.300 align:middle line:84%
isn't, but it's just your karmic
software that is appearing

00:13:19.300 --> 00:13:21.210 align:middle line:84%
in your consciousness
and that you're

00:13:21.210 --> 00:13:23.190 align:middle line:84%
making stories out
of them and you're

00:13:23.190 --> 00:13:25.010 align:middle line:90%
living these stories out.

00:13:25.010 --> 00:13:27.210 align:middle line:84%
And you get so caught
up in the melodrama

00:13:27.210 --> 00:13:29.310 align:middle line:84%
and the hysteria of the
stories that you actually

00:13:29.310 --> 00:13:30.870 align:middle line:90%
forget who you are.

00:13:30.870 --> 00:13:33.200 align:middle line:84%
It's like going to
a really good movie

00:13:33.200 --> 00:13:36.000 align:middle line:90%
and getting lost in the movie.

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:41.290 align:middle line:84%
And therefore the only way
to come out of this tangled

00:13:41.290 --> 00:13:46.530 align:middle line:84%
hierarchy-- because it is a
tangled hierarchy where we lose

00:13:46.530 --> 00:13:48.030 align:middle line:90%
ourselves in the scenery--

00:13:48.030 --> 00:13:52.250 align:middle line:84%
The seer loses itself
in the scenery.

00:13:52.250 --> 00:13:56.940 align:middle line:84%
The lover loses
himself in the beloved.

00:13:56.940 --> 00:14:00.200 align:middle line:84%
The knower loses
himself or herself

00:14:00.200 --> 00:14:03.870 align:middle line:84%
in the objects of
knowledge, never remembering

00:14:03.870 --> 00:14:06.840 align:middle line:84%
that there is a timeless
factor in the midst

00:14:06.840 --> 00:14:08.940 align:middle line:90%
of every time-bound experience.

00:14:08.940 --> 00:14:10.790 align:middle line:90%
All experience is time-bound.

00:14:10.790 --> 00:14:13.910 align:middle line:84%
It has a beginning, a
middle, and an ending.

00:14:13.910 --> 00:14:17.230 align:middle line:84%
But in the midst of all this,
there's a timeless factor.

00:14:17.230 --> 00:14:20.190 align:middle line:90%
It's the experiencer.

00:14:20.190 --> 00:14:25.560 align:middle line:84%
And the experiencer is
the "I" inside, not just

00:14:25.560 --> 00:14:28.510 align:middle line:84%
the personal "I," but
the collective "I"

00:14:28.510 --> 00:14:30.280 align:middle line:90%
and the universal "I."

00:14:30.280 --> 00:14:33.730 align:middle line:84%
That if I start to peel
the layers of my soul,

00:14:33.730 --> 00:14:38.900 align:middle line:84%
I'll go beyond my
constricted fabrication--

00:14:38.900 --> 00:14:42.300 align:middle line:84%
the constricted self-identity
that I have-- and I'll

00:14:42.300 --> 00:14:45.350 align:middle line:90%
discover who I really am.

00:14:45.350 --> 00:14:47.555 align:middle line:84%
And this is the
essence of Vedanta.

00:14:47.555 --> 00:14:50.150 align:middle line:84%
And Vedanta says there
are four ways to do it.

00:14:50.150 --> 00:14:51.770 align:middle line:90%
It's as simple as that.

00:14:51.770 --> 00:14:54.390 align:middle line:84%
The first is called
Karma Yoga, which

00:14:54.390 --> 00:14:58.950 align:middle line:84%
is to be always
reminding yourself

00:14:58.950 --> 00:15:01.740 align:middle line:84%
that no matter what you're
doing, you're not doing it.

00:15:01.740 --> 00:15:03.730 align:middle line:90%
It's God.

00:15:03.730 --> 00:15:04.820 align:middle line:90%
God does everything.

00:15:04.820 --> 00:15:07.840 align:middle line:84%
There is only God, and
this is the machinery

00:15:07.840 --> 00:15:11.580 align:middle line:84%
through which that divine
intelligence is working.

00:15:11.580 --> 00:15:15.690 align:middle line:84%
So the essence of Karma Yoga
is to be established in being

00:15:15.690 --> 00:15:17.840 align:middle line:90%
and perform action.

00:15:17.840 --> 00:15:20.910 align:middle line:84%
Yogastha Kuru Karmani
as Lord Krishna

00:15:20.910 --> 00:15:23.010 align:middle line:90%
says in the Bhagavad Gita.

00:15:23.010 --> 00:15:26.240 align:middle line:84%
The second way to
find the truth--

00:15:26.240 --> 00:15:30.090 align:middle line:84%
to find the nature of
reality-- is through love--

00:15:30.090 --> 00:15:35.470 align:middle line:84%
the experience of love, which
is Bhakti Yoga, or devotion.

00:15:35.470 --> 00:15:38.110 align:middle line:84%
And it's the simplest
and most enjoyable,

00:15:38.110 --> 00:15:40.340 align:middle line:84%
but it gets you
to the same place.

00:15:40.340 --> 00:15:46.700 align:middle line:84%
So that's the second
means to find the truth.

00:15:46.700 --> 00:15:49.330 align:middle line:84%
Because love is the
ultimate reality.

00:15:49.330 --> 00:15:51.440 align:middle line:90%
And love is not a mere emotion.

00:15:51.440 --> 00:15:52.980 align:middle line:90%
Love is not a mere sentiment.

00:15:52.980 --> 00:15:55.750 align:middle line:84%
It's the ultimate truth
at the heart of creation.

00:15:55.750 --> 00:15:57.980 align:middle line:84%
And the ultimate truth
at the heart of creation

00:15:57.980 --> 00:16:02.320 align:middle line:84%
is that we are all the same
being in different disguises.

00:16:02.320 --> 00:16:05.090 align:middle line:84%
When we feel that,
then it becomes

00:16:05.090 --> 00:16:08.210 align:middle line:90%
impossible to hurt or be hurt.

00:16:08.210 --> 00:16:12.880 align:middle line:84%
What the Buddha refers
to as compassion

00:16:12.880 --> 00:16:15.960 align:middle line:84%
is really also the
experiential knowledge

00:16:15.960 --> 00:16:20.920 align:middle line:84%
of love as the ultimate truth
at the heart of creation.

00:16:20.920 --> 00:16:23.110 align:middle line:84%
The third means is
Raja Yoga, which

00:16:23.110 --> 00:16:27.800 align:middle line:84%
is meditation and its
allied disciplines,

00:16:27.800 --> 00:16:32.360 align:middle line:84%
all the different
types of ways to dive

00:16:32.360 --> 00:16:34.290 align:middle line:84%
into the gap between
our thoughts,

00:16:34.290 --> 00:16:38.470 align:middle line:84%
to go beyond the secret
passages and the dark alleys

00:16:38.470 --> 00:16:44.120 align:middle line:84%
of our minds and find this part
of ourselves that does not die.

00:16:44.120 --> 00:16:46.900 align:middle line:84%
And that is the
discipline of Raja Yoga,

00:16:46.900 --> 00:16:52.170 align:middle line:84%
the meditation and its allied
principles, or techniques.

00:16:52.170 --> 00:16:55.420 align:middle line:84%
And the fourth means is
what is called Gyan Yoga.

00:16:55.420 --> 00:17:00.660 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, I've lost myself
in that for my entire life.

00:17:00.660 --> 00:17:03.090 align:middle line:84%
Gyan Yoga is the
intellectual approach,

00:17:03.090 --> 00:17:06.280 align:middle line:84%
which is also called the
razor's edge, because you're

00:17:06.280 --> 00:17:09.770 align:middle line:84%
using the intellect to
go beyond the intellect

00:17:09.770 --> 00:17:13.140 align:middle line:84%
and that in itself
seems to be a paradox.

00:17:13.140 --> 00:17:16.079 align:middle line:84%
But it's possible
to use the intellect

00:17:16.079 --> 00:17:19.040 align:middle line:84%
and go beyond the
intellect ultimately,

00:17:19.040 --> 00:17:20.910 align:middle line:90%
to go beyond the rational way.

00:17:20.910 --> 00:17:23.760 align:middle line:84%
And that, essentially,
is all of Vedanta.

00:17:23.760 --> 00:17:27.510 align:middle line:84%
All the 112 Upanishads,
somehow or the other,

00:17:27.510 --> 00:17:31.180 align:middle line:84%
talk around these
few principles.

00:17:31.180 --> 00:17:35.480 align:middle line:84%
If one has gotten close to
the event horizon, which

00:17:35.480 --> 00:17:40.080 align:middle line:84%
is called enlightenment in
both the Vedantic tradition

00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:44.170 align:middle line:84%
and the Buddhist tradition,
then that experiential knowledge

00:17:44.170 --> 00:17:49.410 align:middle line:84%
of immortality
solves all suffering,

00:17:49.410 --> 00:17:51.960 align:middle line:84%
because you find out
who you really are.

00:17:51.960 --> 00:17:55.930 align:middle line:84%
As the Sufi poet Rumi has
said in one of his most

00:17:55.930 --> 00:17:59.220 align:middle line:84%
elegant poems-- he says, by
God, when you see your beauty,

00:17:59.220 --> 00:18:01.460 align:middle line:90%
you'll be the idol of yourself.

00:18:01.460 --> 00:18:05.450 align:middle line:84%
I've just done a new
translation of Tagore's poems.

00:18:05.450 --> 00:18:09.820 align:middle line:84%
And I chose his poems on the
phenomenon and the experience

00:18:09.820 --> 00:18:14.070 align:middle line:84%
of death because I've always
wondered what would it

00:18:14.070 --> 00:18:18.980 align:middle line:84%
be like to be in that
place in your consciousness

00:18:18.980 --> 00:18:24.190 align:middle line:84%
where you have lost all
fear and can embrace death

00:18:24.190 --> 00:18:32.990 align:middle line:84%
as lovingly and in as
much a celebratory mood

00:18:32.990 --> 00:18:37.210 align:middle line:90%
as you can approach life.

00:18:37.210 --> 00:18:40.080 align:middle line:84%
You can only do it if
you have come home.

00:18:40.080 --> 00:18:42.610 align:middle line:84%
And so what I'd like
to do before I end

00:18:42.610 --> 00:18:44.610 align:middle line:84%
is read to you
about three or four

00:18:44.610 --> 00:18:47.920 align:middle line:84%
of these contemporary
translations

00:18:47.920 --> 00:18:51.360 align:middle line:84%
that I have just
done from Tagore.

00:18:51.360 --> 00:18:55.420 align:middle line:84%
And I'll wear my fancy
glasses to do that.

00:18:55.420 --> 00:18:59.900 align:middle line:84%
But you can see what it
must be to be in that place.

00:18:59.900 --> 00:19:03.210 align:middle line:84%
These poems were written by
the Indian poet Tagore, who

00:19:03.210 --> 00:19:07.270 align:middle line:90%
won the Nobel Prize in 1913.

00:19:07.270 --> 00:19:11.010 align:middle line:84%
Bengali poet, who
was not just a poet.

00:19:11.010 --> 00:19:13.840 align:middle line:84%
He was a real Rishi,
he was a real seer,

00:19:13.840 --> 00:19:17.100 align:middle line:84%
and he had really
understood Vedanta.

00:19:17.100 --> 00:19:19.260 align:middle line:84%
And towards the end
of his life, when

00:19:19.260 --> 00:19:24.422 align:middle line:84%
he was approaching his so-called
death, this is what he wrote.

00:19:24.422 --> 00:19:26.630 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like to read you--
just for a minute or two--

00:19:26.630 --> 00:19:28.050 align:middle line:90%
what he said.

00:19:28.050 --> 00:19:30.390 align:middle line:84%
He said, "I know
that the day will

00:19:30.390 --> 00:19:35.130 align:middle line:84%
come when my sight of
this earth shall be lost,

00:19:35.130 --> 00:19:37.590 align:middle line:84%
and life will take
its leave in silence,

00:19:37.590 --> 00:19:42.570 align:middle line:84%
drawing the last
curtain over my eyes.

00:19:42.570 --> 00:19:48.690 align:middle line:84%
Yet stars will watch at night,
and morning rise as before,

00:19:48.690 --> 00:19:55.420 align:middle line:84%
and hours heave like sea waves
casting up pleasures and pains.

00:19:55.420 --> 00:19:58.420 align:middle line:84%
When I think of this
end of my moments,

00:19:58.420 --> 00:20:00.400 align:middle line:84%
the barrier of
the moments breaks

00:20:00.400 --> 00:20:04.280 align:middle line:84%
and I see by the light
of death your world

00:20:04.280 --> 00:20:06.910 align:middle line:90%
with its careless treasures.

00:20:06.910 --> 00:20:12.950 align:middle line:84%
Rare is its lowliest seat,
rare is its meanest of lives.

00:20:12.950 --> 00:20:17.950 align:middle line:84%
Things that I longed for in
vain and things that I got--

00:20:17.950 --> 00:20:19.770 align:middle line:90%
let them pass.

00:20:19.770 --> 00:20:22.620 align:middle line:84%
Let me but truly
possess the things

00:20:22.620 --> 00:20:26.615 align:middle line:84%
that I ever spurned
and overlooked."

00:20:26.615 --> 00:20:28.750 align:middle line:84%
Other people have said
that if you were aware

00:20:28.750 --> 00:20:33.310 align:middle line:84%
that death is stalking you
right now-- I look behind myself

00:20:33.310 --> 00:20:36.390 align:middle line:84%
and the Prince of Death is
stalking me, and, in fact,

00:20:36.390 --> 00:20:39.930 align:middle line:84%
if I look back
again, it's closer.

00:20:39.930 --> 00:20:42.240 align:middle line:84%
If I was aware that
death is stalking me

00:20:42.240 --> 00:20:44.600 align:middle line:84%
in every moment of
my life, my life

00:20:44.600 --> 00:20:49.070 align:middle line:84%
would be magical because I
would change my priorities.

00:20:49.070 --> 00:20:52.680 align:middle line:84%
As he says, "things
that I longed for

00:20:52.680 --> 00:20:55.820 align:middle line:84%
and things that I
got-- let them pass.

00:20:55.820 --> 00:20:58.500 align:middle line:84%
Let me but truly
possess the things

00:20:58.500 --> 00:21:02.100 align:middle line:84%
that I ever spurned
and overlooked."

00:21:02.100 --> 00:21:06.040 align:middle line:84%
Here, again, he says--
and look at the splendor

00:21:06.040 --> 00:21:09.680 align:middle line:84%
and magnificence of his
mood as he approaches

00:21:09.680 --> 00:21:13.390 align:middle line:84%
his final moments-- "At
this time of my parting,

00:21:13.390 --> 00:21:15.560 align:middle line:90%
wish me good luck, my friends!

00:21:15.560 --> 00:21:20.580 align:middle line:84%
The sky is flushed with the
dawn and my path lies beautiful.

00:21:20.580 --> 00:21:24.110 align:middle line:84%
Ask not what I have
with me to take there.

00:21:24.110 --> 00:21:29.920 align:middle line:84%
I start on my journey with empty
hands and an expectant heart.

00:21:29.920 --> 00:21:33.480 align:middle line:84%
I shall put on my
wedding garland.

00:21:33.480 --> 00:21:37.260 align:middle line:84%
Mine is not the red-brown
dress of the traveler,

00:21:37.260 --> 00:21:39.560 align:middle line:84%
and though there are
dangers on the way

00:21:39.560 --> 00:21:42.780 align:middle line:90%
I have no fear in my mind.

00:21:42.780 --> 00:21:46.740 align:middle line:84%
The evening star will come
out when my voyage is done

00:21:46.740 --> 00:21:49.640 align:middle line:84%
and the plaintive notes
of the twilight melodies

00:21:49.640 --> 00:21:54.870 align:middle line:84%
will be struck up from
the King's highway."

00:21:54.870 --> 00:21:57.000 align:middle line:90%
And one or two more--

00:21:57.000 --> 00:22:00.070 align:middle line:84%
"I was not aware of the
moment when I first crossed

00:22:00.070 --> 00:22:02.800 align:middle line:90%
the threshold of this life.

00:22:02.800 --> 00:22:05.970 align:middle line:84%
What was the power
that made me open out

00:22:05.970 --> 00:22:11.450 align:middle line:84%
into this vast mystery like a
bud in the forest at midnight?

00:22:11.450 --> 00:22:13.900 align:middle line:84%
When in the morning I
looked upon the light,

00:22:13.900 --> 00:22:18.620 align:middle line:84%
I felt in a moment that I was
no stranger in this world,

00:22:18.620 --> 00:22:21.900 align:middle line:84%
that the inscrutable
without name and form

00:22:21.900 --> 00:22:26.320 align:middle line:84%
had taken me in its arms in
the form of my own mother.

00:22:26.320 --> 00:22:29.880 align:middle line:84%
Even so, in death
the same unknown

00:22:29.880 --> 00:22:32.720 align:middle line:90%
will appear as ever known to me.

00:22:32.720 --> 00:22:35.870 align:middle line:84%
And because I love
this life, I know

00:22:35.870 --> 00:22:38.470 align:middle line:90%
I shall love death as well.

00:22:38.470 --> 00:22:41.820 align:middle line:84%
The child cries out when
from the right breast

00:22:41.820 --> 00:22:44.960 align:middle line:84%
the mother takes it away
in the very next moment

00:22:44.960 --> 00:22:49.510 align:middle line:84%
to find in the left
one its consolation."

00:22:49.510 --> 00:22:51.230 align:middle line:90%
And the final one--

00:22:51.230 --> 00:22:55.460 align:middle line:84%
"When I go from hence, let
this be my parting word,

00:22:55.460 --> 00:22:58.870 align:middle line:84%
that what I have seen
is unsurpassable.

00:22:58.870 --> 00:23:02.620 align:middle line:84%
I have tasted of the hidden
honey of this lotus that

00:23:02.620 --> 00:23:07.530 align:middle line:84%
expands on the ocean of life
and light, and so I am blessed.

00:23:07.530 --> 00:23:09.830 align:middle line:90%
Let this be my parting word.

00:23:09.830 --> 00:23:13.920 align:middle line:84%
In this playhouse of infinite
forms, I have had my play

00:23:13.920 --> 00:23:18.360 align:middle line:84%
and here I have caught sight
of him that is formless.

00:23:18.360 --> 00:23:21.130 align:middle line:84%
My whole body and
my whole limbs have

00:23:21.130 --> 00:23:24.950 align:middle line:84%
thrilled with his touch
who is beyond touch.

00:23:24.950 --> 00:23:28.340 align:middle line:84%
And if the end comes
here, let it come.

00:23:28.340 --> 00:23:31.020 align:middle line:90%
Let this be my parting word."

00:23:31.020 --> 00:23:32.028 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

00:23:32.028 --> 00:23:33.492 align:middle line:90%
>>Thank you, Deepak.

00:23:33.492 --> 00:23:36.944 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:23:36.944 --> 00:23:42.880 align:middle line:90%


00:23:42.880 --> 00:23:44.680 align:middle line:84%
What I feel in my
heart really is

00:23:44.680 --> 00:23:49.080 align:middle line:84%
like a feeling of
tribute to India,

00:23:49.080 --> 00:23:54.060 align:middle line:84%
to the great Mahabharata,
great Mother India.

00:23:54.060 --> 00:23:59.890 align:middle line:84%
Because somehow in the dawn
of the world-- 2,500 years ago

00:23:59.890 --> 00:24:04.090 align:middle line:84%
or 3,000 years ago-- the dawn of
this recent era of the world--

00:24:04.090 --> 00:24:09.660 align:middle line:84%
somehow India is the great
place where people really saw

00:24:09.660 --> 00:24:12.050 align:middle line:90%
most deeply, I think, really.

00:24:12.050 --> 00:24:14.650 align:middle line:84%
This American, Euro
American culture,

00:24:14.650 --> 00:24:18.510 align:middle line:84%
the sort of product of New York
that produced New York, that

00:24:18.510 --> 00:24:22.230 align:middle line:84%
produced some
aspects of ourselves,

00:24:22.230 --> 00:24:25.540 align:middle line:84%
our conditioning is based
in the Mediterranean.

00:24:25.540 --> 00:24:28.380 align:middle line:84%
Things of itself, as coming
from the Mediterranean.

00:24:28.380 --> 00:24:33.400 align:middle line:84%
But actually the Mediterranean
was connected by a toll road,

00:24:33.400 --> 00:24:35.947 align:middle line:84%
like the superhighway
of that time that

00:24:35.947 --> 00:24:37.405 align:middle line:84%
was maintained by
the Achaemenids--

00:24:37.405 --> 00:24:41.320 align:middle line:84%
the Persians-- which went
right to the Indus River.

00:24:41.320 --> 00:24:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And every conqueror worth their
salt in the Mediterranean world

00:24:45.690 --> 00:24:49.570 align:middle line:84%
wanted nothing better but to go
to India and conquer something.

00:24:49.570 --> 00:24:51.280 align:middle line:84%
They didn't know
what, but they knew

00:24:51.280 --> 00:24:54.690 align:middle line:84%
they wanted to get there because
they knew that people in India

00:24:54.690 --> 00:24:56.178 align:middle line:90%
were having more fun.

00:24:56.178 --> 00:24:57.492 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:24:57.492 --> 00:24:58.506 align:middle line:90%


00:24:58.506 --> 00:25:00.130 align:middle line:84%
And they wanted, of
course, to go ahead

00:25:00.130 --> 00:25:01.394 align:middle line:90%
and grab that themselves.

00:25:01.394 --> 00:25:03.310 align:middle line:84%
They were there with
their olives and Retsina,

00:25:03.310 --> 00:25:07.390 align:middle line:84%
and they were dreaming of
2,500 varieties of mango.

00:25:07.390 --> 00:25:08.390 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:25:08.390 --> 00:25:09.190 align:middle line:90%


00:25:09.190 --> 00:25:13.080 align:middle line:84%
Now, interestingly, that
land of such a great wealth--

00:25:13.080 --> 00:25:18.860 align:middle line:84%
by far the greatest illuvia
of Eurasia-- the Ma Harrappan

00:25:18.860 --> 00:25:23.170 align:middle line:84%
civilization-- Mohenjo-daro--
the five rivers of the Indus--

00:25:23.170 --> 00:25:26.430 align:middle line:84%
was at its height
15 times larger

00:25:26.430 --> 00:25:30.180 align:middle line:84%
than ancient Egypt, a larger
illuvium with more people

00:25:30.180 --> 00:25:33.150 align:middle line:84%
and more wealth and
more produce and so on.

00:25:33.150 --> 00:25:35.010 align:middle line:84%
And therefore it is
in such a country

00:25:35.010 --> 00:25:39.730 align:middle line:84%
that-- such a land--
that people first came

00:25:39.730 --> 00:25:43.890 align:middle line:90%
to both Veda and then Vedanta.

00:25:43.890 --> 00:25:45.910 align:middle line:90%
Veda meaning knowledge.

00:25:45.910 --> 00:25:48.250 align:middle line:84%
Vedanta meaning, in a way,
the end of knowledge--

00:25:48.250 --> 00:25:50.340 align:middle line:84%
the final conclusion
of knowledge.

00:25:50.340 --> 00:25:53.790 align:middle line:84%
It occurs to me,
too, that somehow

00:25:53.790 --> 00:25:55.360 align:middle line:84%
one of the great
Vedantists really

00:25:55.360 --> 00:25:59.170 align:middle line:84%
was Buddha in the sense that
the Vedantic revolution,

00:25:59.170 --> 00:26:01.930 align:middle line:84%
you could say, in the middle
of the first millennium

00:26:01.930 --> 00:26:04.020 align:middle line:84%
before the Common Era--
or starting, really,

00:26:04.020 --> 00:26:05.686 align:middle line:84%
at the beginning of
the first millennium

00:26:05.686 --> 00:26:08.050 align:middle line:84%
before the Common Era but
ending in the middle--

00:26:08.050 --> 00:26:17.080 align:middle line:84%
was the time when people threw
off the first level of God--

00:26:17.080 --> 00:26:19.540 align:middle line:84%
the god, the protector,
the tribal god,

00:26:19.540 --> 00:26:22.040 align:middle line:84%
god the one who is
somehow connected

00:26:22.040 --> 00:26:24.010 align:middle line:90%
with your fight for survival.

00:26:24.010 --> 00:26:26.150 align:middle line:84%
Because in India at
that time, survival

00:26:26.150 --> 00:26:27.860 align:middle line:90%
became relatively easy.

00:26:27.860 --> 00:26:30.640 align:middle line:84%
Things were relatively
well-organized.

00:26:30.640 --> 00:26:34.070 align:middle line:84%
Life was more gentle really
actually in that place.

00:26:34.070 --> 00:26:36.430 align:middle line:84%
And so people threw
off that and they

00:26:36.430 --> 00:26:41.189 align:middle line:84%
decided that the human
being need not fear reality.

00:26:41.189 --> 00:26:42.730 align:middle line:84%
And they decided
that the human being

00:26:42.730 --> 00:26:44.670 align:middle line:90%
was capable of knowing reality.

00:26:44.670 --> 00:26:46.320 align:middle line:90%
This was the great insight.

00:26:46.320 --> 00:26:48.580 align:middle line:84%
Do you realize,
Deepak, in 10 minutes

00:26:48.580 --> 00:26:51.549 align:middle line:84%
you brilliantly conveyed
the essence of Vedanta?

00:26:51.549 --> 00:26:53.340 align:middle line:84%
And then the very first
thing that you said

00:26:53.340 --> 00:26:55.580 align:middle line:84%
was everything was
contained, too,

00:26:55.580 --> 00:26:59.020 align:middle line:84%
which is that the only
reason that we suffer

00:26:59.020 --> 00:27:03.800 align:middle line:84%
is that we do not know
what our own reality is.

00:27:03.800 --> 00:27:07.470 align:middle line:84%
And that do not knowing is--
and Buddha put it sometimes,

00:27:07.470 --> 00:27:09.300 align:middle line:84%
he put it to force
just like that.

00:27:09.300 --> 00:27:10.509 align:middle line:90%
There was no difference.

00:27:10.509 --> 00:27:12.800 align:middle line:84%
The first thing-- I want to
definitively announce there

00:27:12.800 --> 00:27:16.249 align:middle line:84%
is no difference between
Buddha Dharma and Vedanta.

00:27:16.249 --> 00:27:17.290 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely no difference.

00:27:17.290 --> 00:27:20.409 align:middle line:84%
Some semantic confusion
people attach to,

00:27:20.409 --> 00:27:21.825 align:middle line:84%
but really there
is no difference.

00:27:21.825 --> 00:27:26.560 align:middle line:90%


00:27:26.560 --> 00:27:31.080 align:middle line:84%
The crux and the essence of
it is that this not knowing

00:27:31.080 --> 00:27:37.310 align:middle line:84%
is not merely just like I don't
know what is in that pipe.

00:27:37.310 --> 00:27:40.740 align:middle line:84%
I do not know what
is behind that wall.

00:27:40.740 --> 00:27:43.820 align:middle line:84%
That sort of not knowing
doesn't really hurt me.

00:27:43.820 --> 00:27:49.850 align:middle line:84%
The kind of not knowing is that
I think I do know what I am,

00:27:49.850 --> 00:27:52.860 align:middle line:90%
I think I do know what you are.

00:27:52.860 --> 00:27:54.250 align:middle line:90%
I'm Bob.

00:27:54.250 --> 00:27:56.660 align:middle line:90%
You are Deepak.

00:27:56.660 --> 00:27:58.780 align:middle line:90%
And Bob is not Deepak.

00:27:58.780 --> 00:28:01.250 align:middle line:90%
And somehow Bob is not you.

00:28:01.250 --> 00:28:03.200 align:middle line:84%
And Bob is like
therefore worrying

00:28:03.200 --> 00:28:07.230 align:middle line:84%
because there's so many more
of you than there is Bob.

00:28:07.230 --> 00:28:09.950 align:middle line:84%
And so if I think you
and Bob are different,

00:28:09.950 --> 00:28:12.490 align:middle line:84%
then it's like, well,
who's going to get whom?

00:28:12.490 --> 00:28:15.020 align:middle line:90%
Who is safe from whom?

00:28:15.020 --> 00:28:16.850 align:middle line:84%
Then I think, maybe
God is not me.

00:28:16.850 --> 00:28:19.050 align:middle line:84%
I think, maybe this
pillar is not me.

00:28:19.050 --> 00:28:20.180 align:middle line:90%
The floor, the objects.

00:28:20.180 --> 00:28:24.680 align:middle line:84%
I misknow myself
as a separate self.

00:28:24.680 --> 00:28:27.720 align:middle line:84%
I misknow the other
as a separate other.

00:28:27.720 --> 00:28:30.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm put in the situation,
therefore put myself

00:28:30.200 --> 00:28:35.110 align:middle line:84%
through this misknowing in
the situation of struggling

00:28:35.110 --> 00:28:37.700 align:middle line:90%
with the universe.

00:28:37.700 --> 00:28:40.200 align:middle line:90%
You struggle with the universe.

00:28:40.200 --> 00:28:41.767 align:middle line:84%
Who do you think
is going to win?

00:28:41.767 --> 00:28:43.780 align:middle line:90%


00:28:43.780 --> 00:28:46.460 align:middle line:84%
You know you're going
to lose, of course.

00:28:46.460 --> 00:28:49.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean, now and
then you're feeling

00:28:49.400 --> 00:28:54.390 align:middle line:84%
a little bit excited or happy
or wearing a Donna Karan suit,

00:28:54.390 --> 00:28:56.775 align:middle line:90%
maybe you think you'll win.

00:28:56.775 --> 00:29:00.030 align:middle line:90%
You know, you feel so good.

00:29:00.030 --> 00:29:03.150 align:middle line:84%
But underneath, you
know you'll lose.

00:29:03.150 --> 00:29:05.800 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, that you
can be a little giddy

00:29:05.800 --> 00:29:07.640 align:middle line:84%
about how it's fine,
but in the long run

00:29:07.640 --> 00:29:09.460 align:middle line:90%
you know you are going to lose.

00:29:09.460 --> 00:29:15.290 align:middle line:84%
Whereas if you know your nature,
you know that we are the same.

00:29:15.290 --> 00:29:16.090 align:middle line:90%
We are one.

00:29:16.090 --> 00:29:17.630 align:middle line:90%
Reality is one.

00:29:17.630 --> 00:29:19.170 align:middle line:90%
You are the universe.

00:29:19.170 --> 00:29:20.200 align:middle line:90%
How can you lose?

00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:23.270 align:middle line:90%
There's no opponent, you see.

00:29:23.270 --> 00:29:26.032 align:middle line:84%
And this is the wonderful
thing about India.

00:29:26.032 --> 00:29:30.120 align:middle line:84%
It comes from India
the idea that we can

00:29:30.120 --> 00:29:33.270 align:middle line:90%
know our way free of suffering.

00:29:33.270 --> 00:29:36.399 align:middle line:84%
Now you could call
it Jnana Yoga,

00:29:36.399 --> 00:29:38.190 align:middle line:84%
you can call it Bhakti
Yoga, this and that,

00:29:38.190 --> 00:29:41.470 align:middle line:84%
but it isn't just intellectual,
because this kind of Jnana

00:29:41.470 --> 00:29:43.430 align:middle line:90%
is not mere intellectual.

00:29:43.430 --> 00:29:46.460 align:middle line:84%
It is, of course,
not not intellectual,

00:29:46.460 --> 00:29:51.730 align:middle line:84%
because knowing the nature
of needs the intellect

00:29:51.730 --> 00:29:53.830 align:middle line:90%
at least to get focused.

00:29:53.830 --> 00:29:57.520 align:middle line:84%
But then through
Raja Yoga method,

00:29:57.520 --> 00:30:01.260 align:middle line:84%
through meditative thing,
through Karma Yoga,

00:30:01.260 --> 00:30:04.080 align:middle line:84%
through acting in a way
that you are acting in tuned

00:30:04.080 --> 00:30:06.910 align:middle line:84%
with everything, and
finally through love--

00:30:06.910 --> 00:30:09.580 align:middle line:84%
because once you know
you are everything then

00:30:09.580 --> 00:30:13.510 align:middle line:84%
you're way of experiencing
energy-wise being everything

00:30:13.510 --> 00:30:15.640 align:middle line:90%
is the same thing as love.

00:30:15.640 --> 00:30:17.250 align:middle line:90%
Why do we like being in love?

00:30:17.250 --> 00:30:20.700 align:middle line:84%
Because, remember,
when we're not in love

00:30:20.700 --> 00:30:22.990 align:middle line:84%
we're all alone
against the universe

00:30:22.990 --> 00:30:26.020 align:middle line:84%
and it's outdoing
us all the time.

00:30:26.020 --> 00:30:30.970 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly we feel one with
another being-- usually is

00:30:30.970 --> 00:30:32.070 align:middle line:90%
all we can manage.

00:30:32.070 --> 00:30:33.375 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:30:33.375 --> 00:30:34.680 align:middle line:90%


00:30:34.680 --> 00:30:39.870 align:middle line:84%
And it's usually also
temporary because we,

00:30:39.870 --> 00:30:41.870 align:middle line:84%
for that moment where
we're really happy in love

00:30:41.870 --> 00:30:44.290 align:middle line:84%
is where we're only
living for the happiness

00:30:44.290 --> 00:30:46.010 align:middle line:90%
of the other being.

00:30:46.010 --> 00:30:48.600 align:middle line:84%
We lose ourselves
in the beloved.

00:30:48.600 --> 00:30:51.090 align:middle line:90%
We die in the beloved.

00:30:51.090 --> 00:30:52.200 align:middle line:90%
We do.

00:30:52.200 --> 00:30:55.080 align:middle line:84%
And then at a certain point,
we feel, that's enough of that.

00:30:55.080 --> 00:30:58.190 align:middle line:84%
How much are they
losing themself in me?

00:30:58.190 --> 00:31:00.410 align:middle line:84%
And then immediately the
separation is reaffirmed.

00:31:00.410 --> 00:31:02.540 align:middle line:84%
And then it's like,
who is more with who?

00:31:02.540 --> 00:31:05.770 align:middle line:84%
And then it's endless
dissatisfaction.

00:31:05.770 --> 00:31:08.780 align:middle line:84%
But that moment, that
expansion of the identity

00:31:08.780 --> 00:31:14.186 align:middle line:84%
to be two or two
as one, imagine,

00:31:14.186 --> 00:31:16.060 align:middle line:84%
therefore, like in the
state of enlightenment

00:31:16.060 --> 00:31:19.250 align:middle line:84%
our actual reality,
our actual birthright

00:31:19.250 --> 00:31:24.060 align:middle line:84%
as human beings-- as
aware, reflective beings--

00:31:24.060 --> 00:31:27.200 align:middle line:84%
which is that we have
the ability, the right,

00:31:27.200 --> 00:31:29.740 align:middle line:84%
and the natural
tendency to be in love

00:31:29.740 --> 00:31:35.200 align:middle line:84%
with all beings, the entire
universe all of the time.

00:31:35.200 --> 00:31:37.010 align:middle line:90%
God is means.

00:31:37.010 --> 00:31:38.100 align:middle line:90%
God the lover.

00:31:38.100 --> 00:31:42.070 align:middle line:84%
God means being in
love with everything.

00:31:42.070 --> 00:31:46.110 align:middle line:84%
And love, especially also
it means-- remember love--

00:31:46.110 --> 00:31:47.610 align:middle line:84%
you know, Bhakti--
doesn't mean just

00:31:47.610 --> 00:31:49.060 align:middle line:90%
wishing to possess the beloved.

00:31:49.060 --> 00:31:53.150 align:middle line:84%
Love means willing the
happiness of the beloved.

00:31:53.150 --> 00:31:55.450 align:middle line:84%
So it's like the endless
expansion into happiness.

00:31:55.450 --> 00:31:58.390 align:middle line:90%


00:31:58.390 --> 00:32:01.240 align:middle line:90%
So I have to hail India.

00:32:01.240 --> 00:32:05.020 align:middle line:90%
Plato, Socrates was into it.

00:32:05.020 --> 00:32:08.550 align:middle line:84%
He saw the harmony of the
soul and he saw something

00:32:08.550 --> 00:32:10.350 align:middle line:90%
getting out of the cave.

00:32:10.350 --> 00:32:14.360 align:middle line:84%
But he was there with
all those tyrants.

00:32:14.360 --> 00:32:18.350 align:middle line:84%
And all they had was olives
and a little bit of goat burger

00:32:18.350 --> 00:32:22.040 align:middle line:90%
and some Retsina, a few fish.

00:32:22.040 --> 00:32:23.770 align:middle line:90%
No big illuvium.

00:32:23.770 --> 00:32:24.920 align:middle line:90%
No Greek could manage.

00:32:24.920 --> 00:32:28.370 align:middle line:84%
They had to go and conquer
Egypt to get some wheat

00:32:28.370 --> 00:32:30.860 align:middle line:84%
because you can't grow that
much in these non-illuvial

00:32:30.860 --> 00:32:32.947 align:middle line:90%
countries-- seafaring countries.

00:32:32.947 --> 00:32:36.690 align:middle line:90%


00:32:36.690 --> 00:32:39.910 align:middle line:84%
We have to thank India for this
and this rediscovery of India

00:32:39.910 --> 00:32:42.290 align:middle line:90%
today.

00:32:42.290 --> 00:32:45.284 align:middle line:84%
I can confidently announce--
although I'm always

00:32:45.284 --> 00:32:47.700 align:middle line:84%
confidently announcing that
something will happen tomorrow

00:32:47.700 --> 00:32:51.700 align:middle line:84%
which never happens-- that's
been doing this for 40 years.

00:32:51.700 --> 00:32:55.270 align:middle line:90%
And probably it's posthumous.

00:32:55.270 --> 00:32:57.970 align:middle line:84%
Later, after I
attain nirvana or I'm

00:32:57.970 --> 00:33:00.760 align:middle line:84%
reborn again as
an undergraduate.

00:33:00.760 --> 00:33:02.042 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:33:02.042 --> 00:33:03.750 align:middle line:84%
That's why I'm nice
to my undergraduates.

00:33:03.750 --> 00:33:04.550 align:middle line:90%
I try to be.

00:33:04.550 --> 00:33:09.180 align:middle line:90%


00:33:09.180 --> 00:33:12.810 align:middle line:84%
We have not completed our
renaissance in the West.

00:33:12.810 --> 00:33:15.940 align:middle line:84%
The West's renaissance
is just beginning.

00:33:15.940 --> 00:33:19.440 align:middle line:84%
Its first wave was the discovery
of the humanism and naturalism

00:33:19.440 --> 00:33:24.590 align:middle line:84%
of the Greeks, breaking away
from the grip of the church

00:33:24.590 --> 00:33:28.120 align:middle line:84%
and the grip of a
lower idea of God--

00:33:28.120 --> 00:33:30.780 align:middle line:84%
that God the punisher,
God the ruler,

00:33:30.780 --> 00:33:33.760 align:middle line:84%
God is doing this-- that
mostly was dominating people

00:33:33.760 --> 00:33:36.650 align:middle line:84%
feeling that their minds were
unworthy, that they could not

00:33:36.650 --> 00:33:39.350 align:middle line:84%
understand the
nature of reality.

00:33:39.350 --> 00:33:41.850 align:middle line:84%
And we discovered, well,
we can't understand nature,

00:33:41.850 --> 00:33:45.300 align:middle line:84%
but then nature was defined
as material nature--

00:33:45.300 --> 00:33:50.640 align:middle line:84%
the atom, the mathematics,
the geometry, the pivot.

00:33:50.640 --> 00:33:53.220 align:middle line:84%
And so then for
500 years now we've

00:33:53.220 --> 00:33:56.570 align:middle line:84%
been discovering nature--
the human nature and nature.

00:33:56.570 --> 00:33:58.750 align:middle line:84%
And we've been breaking
away from that spirit.

00:33:58.750 --> 00:34:01.380 align:middle line:84%
In fact, we are scared of spirit
because we associate spirit

00:34:01.380 --> 00:34:05.490 align:middle line:84%
with the Inquisition, with
some sort of [INAUDIBLE].

00:34:05.490 --> 00:34:09.178 align:middle line:84%
So we're running
away from the spirit.

00:34:09.178 --> 00:34:10.719 align:middle line:84%
And we think our
renaissance is over.

00:34:10.719 --> 00:34:12.969 align:middle line:84%
And then some people even
say, well, that was no good.

00:34:12.969 --> 00:34:15.949 align:middle line:84%
The rest of the Enlightenment--
it caused a lot of trouble.

00:34:15.949 --> 00:34:19.520 align:middle line:84%
And they're even
giving up, you know.

00:34:19.520 --> 00:34:21.699 align:middle line:84%
But our Renaissance
really gets rolling

00:34:21.699 --> 00:34:23.980 align:middle line:90%
when we rediscover India.

00:34:23.980 --> 00:34:26.860 align:middle line:84%
So this is where I have
to hail to you, Deepak,

00:34:26.860 --> 00:34:29.389 align:middle line:84%
because, in a way, you
are the voice of India.

00:34:29.389 --> 00:34:34.042 align:middle line:84%
And ironically, you are
educated as a Westerner.

00:34:34.042 --> 00:34:36.000 align:middle line:84%
When we did our dialogue
at Columbia, remember,

00:34:36.000 --> 00:34:38.993 align:middle line:84%
it was so funny because
you were doing science

00:34:38.993 --> 00:34:39.909 align:middle line:90%
and I was doing India.

00:34:39.909 --> 00:34:42.325 align:middle line:84%
I was saying, but wait a minute,
Indian science, remember?

00:34:42.325 --> 00:34:44.949 align:middle line:90%
>>Yeah.

00:34:44.949 --> 00:34:46.420 align:middle line:90%
>>It was counterpoint.

00:34:46.420 --> 00:34:51.540 align:middle line:84%
But, you see, India gives us the
courage that we can understand.

00:34:51.540 --> 00:34:53.199 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that preposterous?

00:34:53.199 --> 00:34:56.330 align:middle line:84%
Who do you think-- if you said
today-- you went and announced

00:34:56.330 --> 00:34:58.580 align:middle line:84%
to your employees, to your
friends, to your relatives,

00:34:58.580 --> 00:35:01.740 align:middle line:84%
ah, I understand my
nature, I understand

00:35:01.740 --> 00:35:04.297 align:middle line:84%
the nature of reality-- if
you announced that, what

00:35:04.297 --> 00:35:05.810 align:middle line:90%
do you think they would do?

00:35:05.810 --> 00:35:06.690 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:35:06.690 --> 00:35:07.130 align:middle line:90%


00:35:07.130 --> 00:35:08.780 align:middle line:84%
They would offer you
a dish of Prozac.

00:35:08.780 --> 00:35:09.630 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:35:09.630 --> 00:35:10.430 align:middle line:90%


00:35:10.430 --> 00:35:12.460 align:middle line:84%
Or St. John's Wort,
I hope, or maybe

00:35:12.460 --> 00:35:15.400 align:middle line:90%
just some nice Ayurvedic remedy.

00:35:15.400 --> 00:35:20.370 align:middle line:84%
Because religious,
you can't do that.

00:35:20.370 --> 00:35:23.130 align:middle line:84%
Only God knows that on the
religious side in the West.

00:35:23.130 --> 00:35:24.980 align:middle line:90%
So nobody can know everything.

00:35:24.980 --> 00:35:28.140 align:middle line:84%
And on the scientific
side, you know how they do.

00:35:28.140 --> 00:35:31.590 align:middle line:84%
They get billions of dollars,
and they study and study.

00:35:31.590 --> 00:35:33.965 align:middle line:84%
And then when they run out of
the dollars, they proclaim,

00:35:33.965 --> 00:35:37.070 align:middle line:84%
aha, we learned a
great deal and now we

00:35:37.070 --> 00:35:40.370 align:middle line:84%
know so much more about
how much we don't know.

00:35:40.370 --> 00:35:44.280 align:middle line:90%
So give us another grand.

00:35:44.280 --> 00:35:46.400 align:middle line:84%
Because in principle,
you cannot know.

00:35:46.400 --> 00:35:48.660 align:middle line:90%
You cannot understand.

00:35:48.660 --> 00:35:52.170 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, of course, they do
announce-- when their grant

00:35:52.170 --> 00:35:54.490 align:middle line:84%
providers are getting
discouraged with them--

00:35:54.490 --> 00:35:56.690 align:middle line:84%
they occasionally
announce that, well, we

00:35:56.690 --> 00:35:59.290 align:middle line:84%
will be knowing another
60 years of calculations

00:35:59.290 --> 00:36:00.620 align:middle line:90%
will bear us out.

00:36:00.620 --> 00:36:02.820 align:middle line:84%
We'll have the grand
theory, so give us

00:36:02.820 --> 00:36:07.230 align:middle line:90%
another 60 years to prove it.

00:36:07.230 --> 00:36:09.700 align:middle line:84%
Whereas in India from this
ancient time, they're saying,

00:36:09.700 --> 00:36:11.170 align:middle line:90%
you don't need a machine.

00:36:11.170 --> 00:36:12.520 align:middle line:90%
You don't even need mathematics.

00:36:12.520 --> 00:36:14.290 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's an
ornament mathematic.

00:36:14.290 --> 00:36:15.500 align:middle line:90%
These machines are useful.

00:36:15.500 --> 00:36:16.660 align:middle line:90%
It's all right.

00:36:16.660 --> 00:36:21.470 align:middle line:84%
But you don't need that because
you are the wondrous machine.

00:36:21.470 --> 00:36:24.200 align:middle line:84%
Long before computers
in this cybernetic age,

00:36:24.200 --> 00:36:25.870 align:middle line:84%
you are the wondrous
machine that

00:36:25.870 --> 00:36:29.240 align:middle line:84%
can turn around
in your footsteps,

00:36:29.240 --> 00:36:34.000 align:middle line:84%
look back into yourself, and
fully understand yourself--

00:36:34.000 --> 00:36:37.720 align:middle line:84%
completely understand that
you are not-- there's nothing

00:36:37.720 --> 00:36:41.020 align:middle line:84%
in you separate from the
great self of the universe.

00:36:41.020 --> 00:36:45.150 align:middle line:84%
As a Vedantic would say
and Buddha would say,

00:36:45.150 --> 00:36:48.340 align:middle line:84%
you are selfless with
regard to that petty self.

00:36:48.340 --> 00:36:50.470 align:middle line:84%
And your great self
of selflessness

00:36:50.470 --> 00:36:53.460 align:middle line:84%
is at one with all beings
and has all knowledge

00:36:53.460 --> 00:36:55.840 align:middle line:84%
available to it,
knows everything

00:36:55.840 --> 00:36:58.960 align:middle line:90%
by being one with everything.

00:36:58.960 --> 00:37:01.547 align:middle line:84%
And when you know that-- and
that's what I always-- I'm

00:37:01.547 --> 00:37:03.880 align:middle line:84%
always thinking-- there's
Buddha over there, by the way,

00:37:03.880 --> 00:37:06.440 align:middle line:84%
standing over there--
an image-- and there

00:37:06.440 --> 00:37:07.820 align:middle line:90%
is another one sitting.

00:37:07.820 --> 00:37:10.950 align:middle line:84%
And I'm always-- when I look
at Buddha, I'm thinking,

00:37:10.950 --> 00:37:13.500 align:middle line:90%
thank goodness he's smiling.

00:37:13.500 --> 00:37:17.750 align:middle line:84%
Imagine-- now I
understand everything.

00:37:17.750 --> 00:37:25.180 align:middle line:84%
And then the next minute you're
going, oh, no, what a bummer,

00:37:25.180 --> 00:37:26.440 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:37:26.440 --> 00:37:28.730 align:middle line:90%
Then we would all be depressed.

00:37:28.730 --> 00:37:31.490 align:middle line:84%
But instead they said,
well, when you know,

00:37:31.490 --> 00:37:33.160 align:middle line:90%
then you are happy, you see.

00:37:33.160 --> 00:37:35.135 align:middle line:84%
It's only by not knowing
that you're unhappy.

00:37:35.135 --> 00:37:37.050 align:middle line:84%
Do you realize the
vast difference

00:37:37.050 --> 00:37:40.070 align:middle line:90%
in those two possible claims?

00:37:40.070 --> 00:37:43.020 align:middle line:84%
Because if our reality
is in fact happiness,

00:37:43.020 --> 00:37:46.340 align:middle line:84%
if our reality is in fact
love, if our reality is

00:37:46.340 --> 00:37:49.510 align:middle line:84%
in fact wisdom, that
means the more we

00:37:49.510 --> 00:37:54.590 align:middle line:84%
can let go of our false
constructions of unreality,

00:37:54.590 --> 00:38:00.990 align:middle line:84%
the more we collapse actually,
the more happy we become.

00:38:00.990 --> 00:38:04.730 align:middle line:84%
So we don't have to
fight with even--

00:38:04.730 --> 00:38:06.480 align:middle line:84%
I was very happy you
announced that we all

00:38:06.480 --> 00:38:10.100 align:middle line:84%
have Alzheimer's, because when I
can't remember anybody's name--

00:38:10.100 --> 00:38:12.270 align:middle line:84%
I call my children
by the wrong names--

00:38:12.270 --> 00:38:16.440 align:middle line:84%
when I can't remember who I am,
then I must be getting happier.

00:38:16.440 --> 00:38:17.500 align:middle line:90%
I must be getting better.

00:38:17.500 --> 00:38:19.541 align:middle line:84%
I only get miserable when
someone comes and says,

00:38:19.541 --> 00:38:21.510 align:middle line:84%
you should know
exactly this and that.

00:38:21.510 --> 00:38:25.210 align:middle line:84%
Don't forget that
name, that's terrible.

00:38:25.210 --> 00:38:28.860 align:middle line:84%
We don't need to know
someone's name to love them.

00:38:28.860 --> 00:38:30.940 align:middle line:84%
In fact, sometimes by
knowing their name too well

00:38:30.940 --> 00:38:34.690 align:middle line:84%
you might get used to
disliking them, in fact.

00:38:34.690 --> 00:38:36.760 align:middle line:84%
If you forget that you
know-- sometimes I do.

00:38:36.760 --> 00:38:41.560 align:middle line:84%
I meet some people nowadays
and they seem to know me.

00:38:41.560 --> 00:38:45.400 align:middle line:84%
And they say, oh, you're
not mad at me anymore.

00:38:45.400 --> 00:38:46.770 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:38:46.770 --> 00:38:48.840 align:middle line:90%
I say, I guess not.

00:38:48.840 --> 00:38:50.000 align:middle line:90%
Don't tell me what you did.

00:38:50.000 --> 00:38:51.434 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:38:51.434 --> 00:38:54.070 align:middle line:90%


00:38:54.070 --> 00:38:59.320 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, so it is India that
gives us this encouragement.

00:38:59.320 --> 00:39:02.580 align:middle line:84%
And therefore India turned--
in this ancient time--

00:39:02.580 --> 00:39:04.390 align:middle line:84%
in a different direction
than the Greeks

00:39:04.390 --> 00:39:06.840 align:middle line:84%
and then the Romans and
then the Europeans and then

00:39:06.840 --> 00:39:08.330 align:middle line:90%
the Americans.

00:39:08.330 --> 00:39:10.760 align:middle line:84%
They turned-- what I
call-- towards-- they

00:39:10.760 --> 00:39:13.770 align:middle line:90%
did the inward turn.

00:39:13.770 --> 00:39:17.140 align:middle line:84%
They said that the king and
the queen of the sciences

00:39:17.140 --> 00:39:20.320 align:middle line:84%
is the inward science--
the science of how

00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:23.470 align:middle line:84%
to know yourself, how
to know your world,

00:39:23.470 --> 00:39:26.410 align:middle line:84%
how to know the gods, how
to know God-- depending

00:39:26.410 --> 00:39:27.726 align:middle line:90%
on what you mean by it.

00:39:27.726 --> 00:39:29.600 align:middle line:84%
In the Vedanta, they
have this wonderful idea

00:39:29.600 --> 00:39:33.070 align:middle line:84%
they call Nirguna Brahman
and Saguna Brahman-- showing

00:39:33.070 --> 00:39:35.180 align:middle line:84%
how they qualify--
that means qualified

00:39:35.180 --> 00:39:38.680 align:middle line:84%
God-- God with properties,
God with personality,

00:39:38.680 --> 00:39:40.250 align:middle line:90%
God with attitude.

00:39:40.250 --> 00:39:42.500 align:middle line:84%
So it was like putting
a burning bush someplace

00:39:42.500 --> 00:39:44.810 align:middle line:84%
or destroying somebody
who gets him mad.

00:39:44.810 --> 00:39:46.680 align:middle line:84%
He's the kind of
God with attitude.

00:39:46.680 --> 00:39:49.150 align:middle line:84%
But then there's
God beyond attitude.

00:39:49.150 --> 00:39:51.260 align:middle line:84%
And God beyond attitude
is no different from us,

00:39:51.260 --> 00:39:52.843 align:middle line:84%
and therefore nothing
to be afraid of.

00:39:52.843 --> 00:39:57.360 align:middle line:90%


00:39:57.360 --> 00:39:58.370 align:middle line:90%
So anyway, OK.

00:39:58.370 --> 00:40:03.020 align:middle line:84%
So the first klesha, that's my
feeling about the first klesha.

00:40:03.020 --> 00:40:05.490 align:middle line:90%
So now I'll turn it back to you.

00:40:05.490 --> 00:40:08.190 align:middle line:84%
>>I just have to say
one thing, and that

00:40:08.190 --> 00:40:12.900 align:middle line:84%
