you explain consciousness

00:41:49.550 --> 00:41:53.330 align:middle line:84%
and understand this
Vedantic/Buddhist perspective--

00:41:53.330 --> 00:41:58.640 align:middle line:84%
nowhere is there an
explanation for what

00:41:58.640 --> 00:42:07.340 align:middle line:84%
we call free will or insight
or intention or imagination

00:42:07.340 --> 00:42:15.040 align:middle line:84%
or inspiration or creativity
or knowingness or understanding

00:42:15.040 --> 00:42:20.100 align:middle line:90%
or decision-making or meaning.

00:42:20.100 --> 00:42:25.940 align:middle line:84%
The meaning, the understanding,
the insight, the intent--

00:42:25.940 --> 00:42:28.970 align:middle line:84%
no matter how sophisticated
artificial intelligence

00:42:28.970 --> 00:42:31.840 align:middle line:84%
becomes, it doesn't
lie in the program.

00:42:31.840 --> 00:42:34.560 align:middle line:84%
It lies in the consciousness
of the programmer.

00:42:34.560 --> 00:42:35.360 align:middle line:90%
>>Absolutely.

00:42:35.360 --> 00:42:36.854 align:middle line:84%
>>And if you use
symbols-- you say,

00:42:36.854 --> 00:42:38.770 align:middle line:84%
