and the hysteria

00:50:28.160 --> 00:50:32.820 align:middle line:84%
and the anxiety of the dream
because you think it's real.

00:50:32.820 --> 00:50:37.830 align:middle line:84%
And you will remain in it
until you wake up from it.

00:50:37.830 --> 00:50:40.240 align:middle line:84%
And then after you
wake up from it,

00:50:40.240 --> 00:50:43.340 align:middle line:84%
then you'll have
the insight, aha,

00:50:43.340 --> 00:50:46.150 align:middle line:84%
what an interesting
state that was.

00:50:46.150 --> 00:50:50.250 align:middle line:84%
So, of course, we have different
words, bardos and so on.

00:50:50.250 --> 00:50:53.680 align:middle line:84%
But here we wake up
from the waking state

00:50:53.680 --> 00:50:57.920 align:middle line:84%
into what Vedanta calls the
fourth state of consciousness.

00:50:57.920 --> 00:50:59.390 align:middle line:84%
The fourth state
of consciousness

00:50:59.390 --> 00:51:03.500 align:middle line:84%
when you have a first
glimpse of your soul.

00:51:03.500 --> 00:51:07.610 align:middle line:84%
People, when they had that, it's
been very dramatic for them.

00:51:07.610 --> 00:51:09.890 align:middle line:84%
Sir Walt Whitman
says, I must not

00:51:09.890 --> 00:51:12.400 align:middle line:84%
be awake for
everything looks to me

00:51:12.400 --> 00:51:15.550 align:middle line:84%
as it never did before
or else I'm awake

00:51:15.550 --> 00:51:21.280 align:middle line:84%
for the first time and all that
was before was just a dream.

00:51:21.280 --> 00:51:24.480 align:middle line:84%
Gautama Buddha himself--
this lifetime of ours

00:51:24.480 --> 00:51:27.470 align:middle line:84%
is as transient
as autumn clouds.

00:51:27.470 --> 00:51:30.300 align:middle line:84%
To watch the birth
and death of beings

00:51:30.300 --> 00:51:33.650 align:middle line:84%
is like looking at the
movements of a dance.

00:51:33.650 --> 00:51:36.070 align:middle line:84%
A lifetime is like
a flash of lightning

00:51:36.070 --> 00:51:39.190 align:middle line:84%
in the sky rushing
by like a torrent

00:51:39.190 --> 00:51:40.830 align:middle line:90%
down the steep mountain.

00:51:40.830 --> 00:51:44.410 align:middle line:84%
But now I'm awake-- which is
the meaning of the word buddha.

00:51:44.410 --> 00:51:46.860 align:middle line:84%
He's asked at the moment of
his death, are you a prophet?

00:51:46.860 --> 00:51:47.930 align:middle line:90%
He says, no.

00:51:47.930 --> 00:51:50.020 align:middle line:90%
Are you the messiah?

00:51:50.020 --> 00:51:51.280 align:middle line:90%
He says, no.

00:51:51.280 --> 00:51:52.470 align:middle line:90%
He says, who are you?

00:51:52.470 --> 00:51:54.380 align:middle line:90%
He says, I'm awake.

00:51:54.380 --> 00:51:55.180 align:middle line:90%
That's all he says.

00:51:55.180 --> 00:51:58.830 align:middle line:84%
That's the meaning of the word
buddha-- the awakened one.

00:51:58.830 --> 00:52:03.090 align:middle line:84%
Waking up from the
insubstantial reality,

00:52:03.090 --> 00:52:05.490 align:middle line:90%
into glimpsing the soul.

